BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: -- Add your vocabulary text file path here üëáset filePath to "/Users/karina/Downloads/Vocabulary/GRE_8000_Words.txt"set WordsCopy to filePath & "Copy.txt"set fgt to filePath & ".LearningLog.txt"set ifexists to do shell script "[ -f " & WordsCopy & " ] && echo yes || echo no"set ifle to do shell script "[ -f " & fgt & " ] && echo yes || echo no"if ifexists = "no" then	do shell script "cp " & filePath & " " & WordsCopyend ifif ifle = "no" then	do shell script "touch " & fgtend ifdo shell script "sed -i '' '/^\\s*$/d' " & filePathset theWords to do shell script "sort --random-sort " & filePath & " | head -n 1"set tmm to do shell script "date " & quote & "+%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S" & quote & " "do shell script "echo " & quote & theWords & " | " & tmm & quote & " >> " & fgtset wd to "{\"text\":\"" & theWords & "\"," & "\"background_color\": \"255,255,255,255\",\"font_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_size\": 15}"

-- Add your vocabulary text file path here üëáset pathFile to "/Users/karina/Downloads/Vocabulary/GRE_8000_Words.txt"set t to "sort --random-sort " & pathFile & " | head -n 1"set theWords to do shell script tset defaultDelimiters to AppleScript's text item delimitersset AppleScript's text item delimiters to ""set w to every text item of theWordsset AppleScript's text item delimiters to defaultDelimitersset result to ""repeat with r in w	set result to result & "üëâ" & r & "   "end repeatset wd to "{\"text\":\"" & result & "\"," & "\"background_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_color\": \"255,255,255,255\",\"font_size\": 15}"

-- Add your vocabulary text file path here üëáset pathFile to "/Users/karina/Downloads/Vocabulary/GRE_8000_Words.txt"-- Custom the number of words üëáset num to 3set t to "sort --random-sort " & pathFile & " | head -n " & numset theWords to do shell script tset defaultDelimiters to AppleScript's text item delimitersset AppleScript's text item delimiters to ""set w to every text item of theWordsset AppleScript's text item delimiters to defaultDelimitersset result to ""repeat with r in w	set result to result & "üëâ" & r & "   "end repeatset wd to "{\"text\":\"" & result & "\"," & "\"background_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_color\": \"255,255,255,255\",\"font_size\": 15}"

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString:
set d to do shell script "date +%s | cut -c 10"
if d ends with 1 then	return "{\"text\":\"How ever you may work hard, you will have much luck.\",\"background_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_color\":\"100,200,100,255\",\"font_size\": 20}"else if d ends with 2 then	return "{\"text\":\"Genius is an infinite capacity for taking pains.\",\"background_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_color\":\"255,165,0,255\",\"font_size\": 20}"else if d ends with 3 then	return "{\"text\":\"There is no royal road to learning.\",\"background_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_color\":\"255,255,0,255\",\"font_size\": 20}"else if d ends with 4 then	return "{\"text\":\"Victory belongs to the most persevering.\",\"background_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_color\":\"0,255,0,255\",\"font_size\": 20}"else if d ends with 5 then	return "{\"text\":\"There is no short cut in learning English.\",\"background_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_color\":\"0,127,255,255\",\"font_size\": 20}"else if d ends with 6 then	return "{\"text\":\"Knowledge is power.\",\"background_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_color\":\"0,0,255,255\",\"font_size\": 20}"else	return "{\"text\":\"After all, tomorrow is another day.\",\"background_color\": \"0,0,0,255\",\"font_color\":\"139,0,255,255\",\"font_size\": 20}"end if

-- Add your vocabulary text file path here üëáset filePath to "/Users/karina/Downloads/Vocabulary/GRE_8000_Words.txt"set ifexists to do shell script "[ -f " & filePath & ".MyNewWordsList.txt" & " ] && echo yes || echo no"if ifexists = "no" then
	do shell script "touch " & filePath & ".MyNewWordsList.txt"end ifset l to do shell script "awk 'END {print}' " & filePath & ".LearningLog.txt"set ll to do shell script "echo " & quote & l & quote & " |   " & "awk -F " & quote & "[|]" & quote & " '{print $1}'"set cw to do shell script "echo " & quote & ll & quote & " | awk -F " & quote & "[ \\,\\.\\Ôºå\\[\\(\\{\\„Äå\\„Äé\\Ôºö\\:\\;\\Ôºõ\\/\\„ÄÅ]" & quote & " '{print $1}'"set cww to do shell script "sed -n '" & "/" & cw & "/p' " & filePath & ".MyNewWordsList.txt"set n to 0try	if get the length of cww = 0 then		set n_ to n + 1		do shell script "echo " & quote & ll & " &&& " & n_ & quote & " >> " & filePath & ".MyNewWordsList.txt"	else		set ti to do shell script "grep " & cw & " " & filePath & ".MyNewWordsList.txt" & "|awk -F " & quote & " &&& " & quote & " '{print $2}'"		set ti_ to ti + 1		do shell script "sed -i '' '/" & cw & "/" & "d' " & filePath & ".MyNewWordsList.txt"		do shell script "echo " & quote & ll & " &&& " & ti_ & quote & " >> " & filePath & ".MyNewWordsList.txt"	end ifend try
